e 6th king of the Xia dynasty (2070–1600  BC ). (ii) from the first element of the placename Ai Ling (艾陵), the name of a hill (located in Shandong province), the fief of Ai Kong (艾孔), an official in the state of Qi during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ). (iii) from the placename Ai (艾), the name of a fief (located in Jiangxi province) which was granted to an official in the state of Chu during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ). (iv) adopted as a surname by the Qu Jin (去斤), Qu Ai (去艾), and Ai Jin (艾斤) families from the Xianbei ethnic group in northern China during the Northern Wei dynasty (386–534  AD ). (v) from Ai (艾), the name of an ancient state (possibly in present-day Jiangxi province) during the Shang dynasty (1600–1046  BC ).","Chinese: Mandarin form of the surname 愛, meaning ‘love’ in Chinese: (i) said to be traced back to Ai Xie Wu (愛邪勿), prime minister of the state of Huihu (known as Uyghur Empire or Uyghur Khaganate), who was endowed with the surname Ai (愛) by Emperor Wuzong of Tang (814–846  AD ). (ii) a Han Chinese surname for some members of the Aisin Gioro family from the Manchu ethnic group, known as the royal family of the Qing dynasty (1616 – 1911  AD ). (iii) a surname from minority ethnic groups in Taiwan."]}]},{"name":"Ithel","type":"LAST","meanings":["A Welsh name derived from the Greek, signifying 'blooming luxuriantly, flourishing, rich.'. It is from Ithel that we have first the name Ap-Ithel, then by corruption, Bithell and Bethell."],"variants":[{"name":"Bithell","meanings":["Welsh: variant of   Bethel  ."]},{"name":"Bethell","meanings":["Welsh: variant of   Bethel  ."]}]},{"name":"Llwyd","type":"LAST","meanings":["Same as Lhuyd, q v."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Ithel","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Traditional: compound of <i>iud</i> ‘lord, prince’ + <i>hael</i> ‘generous’; borne in the <i>Mabinogi</i> by the son of Llarian."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Fychan","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Welsh: A Welsh name of great antiquity, from vyckan, little, small; i.e. small in stature. Compare the surname Bychan and the Armoric Le Bihan."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Ithel Fychan ab Ithel Llwyd was born in 1211, in Wales as the son of Ithel Llwyd ab Ithel Gam. He had at least 8 sons and 2 daughters with Margaret Brickill. He died about 1311, in Halkyn, Flintshire, Wales, at the age of 101, and was buried in Halkyn, Flintshire, Wales."},"et":{"1211–about 1311":"1211–umbes 1311","1211–1311":"1211–1311","1300–1300":"1300–1300","1241–1341":"1241–1341","1257–1357":"1257–1357","1300–1348":"1300–1348","1300–Male":"1300–Surnud","1300–Female":"1300–Surnud","1310–Female":"1310–Surnud","1315–Male":"1315–Surnud","1320–1352":"1320–1352","–Male":"Surnud","1250–Male":"1250–Surnud","Aft 1257":"pärast 1257","Aft 1300":"pärast 1300","1352":"1352","1341":"1341","1241":"1241","1250":"1250","Abt 1241":"umbes 1241","1315":"1315","1348":"1348","1357":"1357","Abt 1300":"umbes 1300","1257":"1257","1300":"1300","1311":"1311","1211":"1211","1310":"1310","1320":"1320","about 1311":"umbes 1311","of, Halkyn, Flintshire, Wales":"Halkyn, Flintshire, Wales","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Wales":"Wales","Halkyn, Flintshire, Wales":"Halkyn, Flintshire, Wales","of, Cilcain, Flintshire, Wales":"Cilcain, Flintshire, Wales"},"fi":{"1211–about 1311":"1211–noin 1311","1211–1311":"1211–1311","1300–1300":"1300–1300","1241–1341":"1241–1341","1257–1357":"1257–1357","1300–1348":"1300–1348","1300–Male":"1300–Kuollut","1300–Female":"1300–Kuollut","1310–Female":"1310–Kuollut","1315–Male":"1315–Kuollut","1320–1352":"1320–1352","–Male":"Kuollut","1250–Male":"1250–Kuollut","Aft 1257":"1257 jälkeen","Aft 1300":"1300 jälkeen","1352":"1352","1341":"1341","1241":"1241","1250":"1250","Abt 1241":"noin 1241","1315":"1315","1348":"1348","1357":"1357","Abt 1300":"noin 1300","1257":"1257","1300":"1300","1311":"1311","1211":"1211","1